moduleConfigs.about:
From walking the dog to moving around the house - it all counts. If you keep your mobile in your pocket the BreeConnect app will create a picture of your general activity based on your step-count. Information about how many steps you take and your general activity over time gives your care team extra insight into your health, which can be used to inform your care.

Counting how many steps you’ve done will show you and your care team how active you are. All you need to do is keep your phone switched on and in your pocket, hand or bag, and this app will record your steps automatically. Even doing the housework and going around the shops will count.

To track your daily steps, please follow these instructions.

Check you have the Google Fit app installed on your smartphone – this will enable the BreeConnect app to track the steps you take every day. If you do not have the Google Fit app installed, please download it from the Google Play Store.

Please sign into the Google Fit app. You will need to register if you do not have an account. Return to the BreeConnect app and ‘Update’ your steps to pull your steps data from Google Fit into your BreeConnect app.

en.hu_norfolk_notification_title: Tell us about your quality of life
en.hu_norfolk_about: This questionnaire is a tool designed to measure quality of life for people who suffer from diabetic neuropathy. There are 47 questions, the answers to which will help identify which nerves are affected and to what extent. On the following screens, please select the statement that best applies to you.
en.hu_norfolk_info_description: On the following screens, please tap the statement that best describes your health.
en.hu_norfolk_q3text: Do you have any known medical condition that causes pain or weakness?
en.hu_norfolk_q5text: How long have you had any symptoms of neuropathy?
en.hu_norfolk_q6text: Are the symptoms the same on the right as on the left?
en.hu_norfolk_q9text: Are the symptoms usually worse at night?
en.hu_norfolk_q10text: How many medications or other treatments have you used for any of these symptoms (both in the past and presently)?
en.hu_norfolk_q11text: Have you ever been told that you have neuropathy?
en.hu_norfolk_q12text: Have you ever had ulcer(s) on your feet?
en.hu_norfolk_q14text: Have you had any toes (or fingers) amputated?
en.hu_norfolk_q15text: In the past 4 weeks, have you had a problem with involuntary urinating when laughing or coughing?
en.hu_norfolk_q16text: In the past 4 weeks, have you had a problem with obtaining or maintaining erections?
en.hu_norfolk_q16_description: Males only. Skip if not applicable to you.
en.hu_norfolk_q17text: In the past 4 weeks, have you had a problem with vaginal dryness during intercourse?
en.hu_norfolk_q17_description: Females only. Skip if not applicable to you.
en.hu_norfolk_part1_description: Have you had any of the following symptoms in the past 4 weeks?  Please select all that apply.
en.hu_norfolk_part2_description: Answer these questions according to the following scale
en.hu_norfolk_fourweeks_pain_night: In the past 4 weeks, has pain kept you awake or woken you at night?
en.hu_norfolk_fourweeks_touch: In the past 4 weeks, has the touch of bed sheets, clothes, or wearing shoes bothered you?
en.hu_norfolk_fourweeks_feel: In the past 4 weeks, have you burned or injured yourself and been unable to feel it?
en.hu_norfolk_fourweeks_activity: In the past 4 weeks, have any symptoms kept you from doing your usual activities during the day?
en.hu_norfolk_fourweeks_movement: In the past 4 weeks, have you had difficulty doing fine movements with your fingers, like buttoning your clothes, turning pages in a book, picking up coins from a table?
en.hu_norfolk_fourweeks_walk: In the past 4 weeks, have you felt unsteady on your feet when you walk?
en.hu_norfolk_fourweeks_hands: In the past 4 weeks, have you had any problem getting out of a chair without pushing with your hands?
en.hu_norfolk_fourweeks_stairs: In the past 4 weeks, have you had a problem walking down stairs?
en.hu_norfolk_fourweeks_feelFeetWalking: In the past 4 weeks, have you been unable to feel your feet when walking?
en.hu_norfolk_fourweeks_tellWaterHands: In the past 4 weeks, have you been unable to tell hot from cold water with your hands?
en.hu_norfolk_fourweeks_tellWaterFeet: In the past 4 weeks, have you been unable to tell hot from cold water with your feet?
en.hu_norfolk_fourweeks_meals: In the past 4 weeks, have you had a problem with vomiting, particularly after meals (but not due to flu or other illness)?
en.hu_norfolk_fourweeks_controls: In the past 4 weeks, have you had a problem with diarrhea and/or loss of bowel control?
en.hu_norfolk_fourweeks_standup: In the past 4 weeks, have you had a problem with fainting or dizziness when you stand?
en.hu_norfolk_difficultyActivities: In the past 4 weeks, how much difficulty have you had performing the following activities
en.hu_norfolk_toilet: Getting on or off the toilet?
en.hu_norfolk_physicalEmotional_health: In the past 4 weeks, have you had any of the following problems with your work or other regular daily activities as a result of your physical or emotional health?
en.hu_norfolk_cutDown_time: Cut down on the amount of time you spent on work or other activities?
en.hu_norfolk_accomplished: Accomplished less than you would like?
en.hu_norfolk_limited_activities: Were limited in the kind of work or other activities you could perform?
en.hu_norfolk_extra_effort: Had difficulty performing the work/other activities (it took extra effort)?
en.hu_norfolk_general_health: In general, would you say your health now is:
en.hu_norfolk_threeMonth_healthRate: Compared with 3 months ago, how would you rate your health in general now?
en.hu_norfolk_fourWeeks_socialActivities: In the past 4 weeks, to what extent has your physical health interfered with your normal social activities with family, friends, neighbors, or groups?
en.hu_norfolk_fourWeeks_normalWork: In the past 4 weeks, how much did pain interfere with your normal work (including work both outside the home and housework)?
en.hu_norfolk_fourWeeks_shakiness: In the past 4 weeks, how much did weakness or shakiness interfere with your normal work (including work both outside the home and housework)?
en.hu_norfolk_submission_description: Scroll up to change any of your answers. Changing answers may add new questions.
